---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ContactForm from '../../components/ContactForm.astro';
import RelatedServices from '../../components/RelatedServices.astro';
import ServiceAreasLink from '../../components/ServiceAreasLink.astro';
import { SITE_CONFIG } from '../../config';
import { generateServiceSchema } from '../../utils/schema';

const serviceSchema = generateServiceSchema('retaining-walls', 'Professional concrete retaining wall construction in Deptford, NJ. Erosion control and landscaping solutions with free estimates.');
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Concrete Retaining Wall Installation in Deptford, NJ"
  description="Expert concrete retaining wall contractors in Deptford, NJ. Erosion control, drainage management, and landscaping walls. Professional installation for property protection."
  schema={serviceSchema}
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Concrete Retaining Wall Installation in Deptford, New Jersey</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">Professional retaining wall construction for erosion control and landscaping. Durable concrete walls that protect your property.</p>
      <a href="#contact-form" class="cta-primary">Get Free Retaining Wall Estimate</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Retaining Wall Services</h2>
      <p>We build durable concrete retaining walls that control erosion, manage drainage, and enhance your property's appearance.</p>

      <h3>What's Included in Our Retaining Wall Service</h3>
      <p>When you choose Deptford Concrete Contractors for your retaining wall project, you receive comprehensive service:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Free Site Evaluation:</strong> We assess your property, soil conditions, drainage patterns, and erosion issues at no cost</li>
        <li><strong>Wall Design:</strong> Custom retaining wall design that meets structural requirements and addresses your specific needs</li>
        <li><strong>Permit Assistance:</strong> We help navigate the permit process for retaining walls, which may be required for taller walls</li>
        <li><strong>Professional Excavation:</strong> Proper site preparation and excavation to the correct depth for your wall foundation</li>
        <li><strong>Quality Materials:</strong> High-grade concrete and reinforcement materials appropriate for your wall's requirements</li>
        <li><strong>Expert Installation:</strong> Skilled installation by experienced concrete professionals</li>
        <li><strong>Drainage Systems:</strong> Proper drainage behind the wall to prevent water pressure buildup</li>
        <li><strong>Reinforcement:</strong> Appropriate reinforcement based on wall height and soil conditions</li>
        <li><strong>Code Compliance:</strong> All work meets or exceeds local building codes and regulations</li>
        <li><strong>Cleanup:</strong> Complete site cleanup after installation</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Our Retaining Wall Installation Process</h3>
      <p>We follow a detailed process to ensure your retaining wall is built correctly and safely:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Site Evaluation:</strong> We assess your property, including soil conditions, drainage, erosion issues, and local building requirements</li>
        <li><strong>Design & Planning:</strong> We create a wall design that meets structural requirements, addresses your needs, and complies with local codes</li>
        <li><strong>Permit Assistance:</strong> We help secure necessary permits if required (typically for walls over 4 feet)</li>
        <li><strong>Excavation:</strong> Professional excavation to proper depth for wall foundation</li>
        <li><strong>Foundation Preparation:</strong> Proper base preparation and foundation installation for stability</li>
        <li><strong>Reinforcement Placement:</strong> Installation of rebar reinforcement as specified in the design</li>
        <li><strong>Formwork:</strong> Installation of forms to create your wall's shape and dimensions</li>
        <li><strong>Concrete Pouring:</strong> Placement of high-quality concrete mix appropriate for retaining wall use</li>
        <li><strong>Drainage Installation:</strong> Installation of drainage systems behind the wall</li>
        <li><strong>Finishing:</strong> Proper finishing and texturing of the wall surface</li>
        <li><strong>Curing:</strong> Proper curing time to ensure maximum strength and durability</li>
        <li><strong>Final Inspection:</strong> Quality check to ensure your wall meets all standards</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Common Issues Retaining Walls Solve</h3>
      <p>Retaining walls address many critical property protection and landscaping needs:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Erosion Control:</strong> Prevent soil erosion on sloped properties, especially important in areas with heavy rainfall</li>
        <li><strong>Drainage Management:</strong> Control water flow and prevent flooding or water damage to structures</li>
        <li><strong>Property Protection:</strong> Protect buildings, driveways, and other structures from soil movement</li>
        <li><strong>Landscaping Enhancement:</strong> Create level areas for patios, gardens, or other landscaping features</li>
        <li><strong>Increased Usable Space:</strong> Create flat, usable areas on sloped properties</li>
        <li><strong>Safety Concerns:</strong> Prevent dangerous slope failures or collapses that could damage property or cause injury</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>What Happens When You Call</h3>
      <p>Getting your retaining wall installed is straightforward with our streamlined process:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Initial Contact (24-48 Hour Response):</strong> When you reach out via phone or our contact form, we'll respond within 24-48 hours to schedule your free estimate</li>
        <li><strong>Free On-Site Estimate:</strong> We visit your property to assess your needs, evaluate the site, and provide a detailed written estimate</li>
        <li><strong>Project Planning:</strong> Once you approve the estimate, we handle all planning including permits (if needed), material ordering, and scheduling</li>
        <li><strong>Professional Installation:</strong> Our experienced team completes your retaining wall installation efficiently and professionally</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Our Customer Service Promise</h3>
      <p>At Deptford Concrete Contractors, we believe in complete transparency and honest communication:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>No Hidden Fees:</strong> Your written estimate includes all costs - materials, labor, permits, drainage systems, and cleanup - no surprises</li>
        <li><strong>Clear Communication:</strong> We keep you informed at every step, from initial estimate through project completion</li>
        <li><strong>Realistic Timelines:</strong> We provide honest timelines based on project scope and weather conditions - typically 2-4 days for most retaining walls</li>
        <li><strong>Quality Guarantee:</strong> We stand behind our work and ensure your retaining wall meets all quality, safety, and code standards</li>
        <li><strong>Responsive Service:</strong> We respond to questions and concerns promptly, typically within 24-48 hours</li>
        <li><strong>Licensed & Insured:</strong> Full professional coverage protects you and your property throughout the project</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Retaining Wall Investment Factors</h3>
      <p>Understanding what affects your retaining wall investment helps you make informed decisions:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Wall Height:</strong> Taller walls require more materials, deeper foundations, and may need permits</li>
        <li><strong>Wall Length:</strong> Longer walls require more materials and labor</li>
        <li><strong>Soil Conditions:</strong> Challenging soil may require additional reinforcement or deeper foundations</li>
        <li><strong>Drainage Requirements:</strong> Properties with water issues may need more extensive drainage systems</li>
        <li><strong>Reinforcement Needs:</strong> Taller walls or challenging conditions require more reinforcement</li>
        <li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> Difficult access may require special equipment or additional time</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We provide free, detailed estimates that break down all costs so you understand exactly what you're investing in. There are no hidden fees or surprise charges - what we quote is what you pay.</p>

      <h3>Related Services</h3>
      <p>Retaining walls often work with other concrete features:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/services/patios">Patio Installation</a> - Elevated patios with retaining walls</li>
        <li><a href="/services/driveways">Driveway Installation</a> - Driveways with grade changes</li>
        <li><a href="/services/walkways">Walkway Installation</a> - Pathways with retaining walls</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Areas We Serve</h3>
      <p>We provide retaining wall installation services throughout <a href="/locations/deptford-nj">Deptford</a>, <a href="/locations/west-deptford-nj">West Deptford</a>, <a href="/locations/woodbury-nj">Woodbury</a>, <a href="/locations/glassboro-nj">Glassboro</a>, and <a href="/locations">all surrounding Gloucester County communities</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <RelatedServices currentService="retaining-walls" />
  <ServiceAreasLink serviceName="Retaining Walls" />

  <section id="contact-form" class="contact-section">
    <div class="container">
      <ContactForm 
        title="Get Your Free Retaining Wall Estimate"
        service="retaining-walls"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Retaining Wall FAQs</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How tall can a concrete retaining wall be?</h3>
          <p>Retaining wall height depends on soil conditions, design, and local codes. Most residential walls are 3-4 feet, while taller walls may require engineering and permits. We'll assess your needs during the free estimate.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Do I need a permit for a retaining wall?</h3>
          <p>Permit requirements vary by municipality and wall height. Walls over 4 feet typically require permits. We'll check local requirements and assist with permit applications if needed.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How long does retaining wall installation take?</h3>
          <p>Most retaining wall installations take 2-4 days depending on height, length, and complexity. We'll provide a detailed timeline during your free estimate.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Do retaining walls need drainage?</h3>
          <p>Yes, proper drainage behind retaining walls is essential to prevent water pressure buildup that could cause wall failure. We include drainage systems in all our retaining wall installations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can a retaining wall be repaired instead of replaced?</h3>
          <p>It depends on the extent of damage. Minor issues can often be repaired, but significant structural problems may require replacement. We'll assess your wall during the free estimate and recommend the best solution.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

